The semi-perimeter of triangle $ACD$ is $(7 + 15 + 20)/2 = 21$, so by Heron's formula, the area of triangle $ACD$ is $$\sqrt{21 (21 - 7)(21 - 15)(21 - 20)} = \boxed{42}.$$
